# `worker.ts` (OpenNext Cloudflare entry)

- **Do not remove** the first two lines before the `openNextWorker` import:
  1. `//DO NOT REMOVE THE FOLLOWING COMMENT`
  2. `// @ts-ignore — OpenNext writes .open-next/worker.js ...` (suppresses missing module before first build; **`@ts-ignore`** is used instead of `@ts-expect-error` so `tsc` does not fail with TS2578 “unused @ts-expect-error” after `.open-next/worker.js` exists post-build.)
- OpenNext generates `.open-next/worker.js` only after `opennextjs-cloudflare build`. Do **not** delete these lines to “clean up” or satisfy an unused-directive error.
- Do not replace this block with a plain import unless the user explicitly asks.
